        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 5:28PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 527 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Winsted, or 7 miles northeast of Torrington, moving northeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pleasant Valley, Mooreville, Riverton, Mill Brook, New Hartford,
Beech Rock, Grantville, Robertsville, Burrville, Winsted, Colebrook,
Barkhampsted Center, Winchester Center, Nelsons Corner, New Hartford
Center, Barkhamsted, Goose Green, North Colebrook, and Torrington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
